text:
Custom as in alters?

And yeah I'm not a fan of emperor myself. I'll try anything but the few times I played empower the middle people just build and combo off too quickly, even with fairly casual decks
Custom as in cards not by WotC
Ah
Yeah, custom designs.
They're cool from a concept design pov
Like this one
<https://i.redd.it/at3swchmaevz.png>
I wish they would bring back the be a designer competition. Both people that won still work in R&D, and those contests were years ago.
The Great Designer Search? Do you listen to DTW? I thought MaRo said they would do another one eventually.
No I don't. Between studying for certifications and work I don't really have time to listen to a lot of magic podcasts or vidcasts anymore.
I originally wanted to make a podcast with my bf but... it seems like everyone and their sister has one. I feel like I'm just jumping on the hype
Plus I never listen to them myself outside of bill burr lol
Why don't people just pay me money for the gift of my existence! Ugh! (Is what our society is becoming)
You could always listen to Commander Time! (Shameless plug)

In all honesty most of them are just plain boring. Very few of them go deep on interesting cards and tend to talk about common meta occurrences, and I understand why. It's just that I don't particularly find that useful or interesting. If I wanted to laugh, I would go watch old Bill Hicks stand up, but that's not why I would listen/watch those. Being funny just isn't enough for me either.
Voice is a huge thing for me. There's YouTube videos of lore and stuff from mtg I really like but... the voice... ehhh
Yeah that's another problem as well. Desolator and Saffron Olive are among the worst in my opinion. Their voices just grate upon me.
Desolator? Someone actually calls themselves Desolator?
I suppose if someone wants to call themselves Saffron Olive...
Yes, and the personality is as you would expect. He had a respectable fan base at one time until his reputation as an edge lord switched from fame to infamy.
What's an edge lord?
An edge lord is a type of troll that specifically says things to trigger people, but focuses more on personally offending or attacking people.
For instance, he makes common practice of going to other more successful channels and streams just to shit post.
Fedora wearing vape users.
Still wear jnco jeans
Yes, basically.
And bleach their hair.
Studded leather wristbands and haven't shaved their goatee in 2 years
But miraculously have time to go get a tired ass "undercut" haircut.
You seem to be a connoisseur of the genre, <@U33EGB4TX>
There are a few that frequent the lgs.
<@U33EGB4TX> is studying them from a purely anthropological perspective.
His gritty documentary detailing the dirty inner workings of their culture should be finished soon.:joy:
I love people watching. I got my car worked on yesterday so I sat in the food court of the local shopping center and soaked it all I
In
They are the type of people that are constantly looking for Phyrexian Obliterators and Blighsteel Colossus.
Law enforcement calls that loitering or stalking, <@U33EGB4TX>
Not if I'm a patron of their services.
They call that a beard...
